      'art.tw.h3.3':       'Propping & Temporary Structural Support',
      'art.tw.faq.q1':     'When does OHSA Reg 213/91 require P.Eng.-designed temporary works?',
      'art.tw.faq.a1':     'When formwork supports slabs/beams cast at heights greater than 3.0 m; when excavation is deeper than 1.2 m in unstable soil; for all falsework for elevated structures; and for cofferdams and rigging systems over 2,270 kg. Engineer-sealed drawings must be on site.',
      'art.tw.faq.q2':     'What is the difference between formwork and falsework?',
      'art.tw.faq.a2':     'Formwork is the concrete contact surface/molding system. Falsework is the temporary structural system supporting the formwork against wet concrete loads. Both require engineering when height thresholds are exceeded under OHSA Reg 213/91.',
      'art.tw.faq.q3':     'What are the engineer\'s ongoing responsibilities during temporary works?',
      'art.tw.faq.a3':     'Under PEO guidelines, the engineer must provide sealed drawings, specify inspection requirements before loading, and be available for site consultation. Significant deviations from the design must be reviewed and re-sealed before loading the modified system.',
      'art.tw.faq.q4':     'What temporary support is required when excavating near existing buildings?',
      'art.tw.faq.a4':     'OHSA Reg 213/91 s.226 requires a P.Eng. assessment and a shoring/underpinning plan before excavating within 1.5× the depth of adjacent footings. Vibration monitoring and settlement monitoring of adjacent structures are standard Toronto practice.',
      'art.tw.cta.h':      'Temporary Works Engineering Across Ontario',
      'art.tw.cta.p':      'Asvakas Engineering provides OHSA Reg 213/91 compliant designs for formwork, shoring, falsework, and excavation support across Ontario construction projects.',
      'art.tw.sb.cta.h':   'Temporary Works Design',
      'art.tw.sb.cta.p':   'OHSA-compliant P.Eng. designs for formwork, shoring, and excavation support in Ontario.',

