      'art.ss.faq.q1':     'When is shoring required by law in Ontario?',
      'art.ss.faq.a1':     'OHSA Regulation 213/91 requires shoring or sloped excavation walls for any excavation deeper than 1.2 m where workers are present. A P.Eng. must design the shoring system for excavations exceeding 3 m depth or adjacent to structures or roadways.',
      'art.ss.faq.q2':     'What is the difference between shoring and underpinning?',
      'art.ss.faq.a2':     'Shoring is temporary — it retains soil during construction and is removed or abandoned afterward. Underpinning is permanent — it extends an existing foundation deeper to restore or increase its capacity. Both require P.Eng.-sealed engineering in Ontario.',
      'art.ss.faq.q3':     'What shoring system is best for Toronto\'s soil?',
      'art.ss.faq.a3':     'Toronto\'s glacial till (Halton or Elgin Till) and Leda clay typically suit soldier pile and timber lagging for cohesive soils above the water table. Secant pile walls are preferred for deep excavations or sites near the water table. A geotechnical investigation is required to confirm soil conditions and select the right system.',
      'art.ss.faq.q4':     'Do I need a building permit for underpinning?',
      'art.ss.faq.a4':     'Yes. Underpinning of an existing foundation is a structural alteration requiring a building permit in Ontario. Permit submissions must include P.Eng.-sealed structural drawings showing the underpinning design, load transfers, and foundation details.',
      'art.ss.faq.q5':     'How long does shoring design take?',
      'art.ss.faq.a5':     'Typically 2–4 weeks from receipt of geotechnical data and site geometry for a standard soldier pile system. More complex secant pile or anchor systems may take 4–8 weeks including coordination with the geotechnical engineer on anchor capacity testing and specialty contractor submittals.',
      'art.ss.cta.h':      'Shoring & Temporary Works Engineering Across Ontario',
      'art.ss.cta.p':      'Asvakas Engineering provides P.Eng.-sealed shoring designs, underpinning engineering, and OHSA 213/91-compliant field review for excavation projects across Toronto and the GTA.',
      'art.ss.sb.cta.h':   'Ontario Temporary Works',
      'art.ss.sb.cta.p':   'P.Eng.-sealed shoring drawings, underpinning design, and OHSA 213/91-compliant documentation for Ontario construction projects.',

